Kayode Idowu, Maiduguri  The Borno State Government has clamped down on 10 filling stations in Maiduguri for allegedly hoarding petroleum products. The government, in a statement by the Secretary to the State Government, Alhaji Usman Jidda, also threatened to close down any other filling station caught with any illegal act, especially hoarding of petroleum products or selling above the approved pump price. He statement read in part, “The fueling stations are also engaged in economic sabotage by hoarding petroleum products, and selling them above the approved price, the actions of these fueling stations, their owners and operators is condemnable.” Copyright PUNCH.
